{
  "texts": [
    "Next, an (arg)max operation is performed to count the number of best matches, and the counts for each group's dictionary are increased.",
    "The main hyperparameters to consider are the number of groups and the number of kernels per group, with default values of g = 64 and k = 8.",
    "Hydra is applied to both the time series and its first-order differences.",
    "The best results in Dempster et al. (2022) come from concatenating features from Hydra with features from MultiROCKET to form its pipeline.",
    "We call this classifier MultiROCKET-Hydra."
  ]
}